            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat, then once hot, add the<strong> chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to break down</p><p>Once the tomato has started to break down, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-15 min, stirring frequently, or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>warming tomato jam</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1619713277942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1619713277942-x400.jpg",
